# Manual Code Review Checkpoints

When the user asks for a manual code review:

- Use the code-reviewer skill.
- Do not fix code automatically.
- Review the diff and relevant docs.
- Return a structured review report.
- Use severity labels: BLOCKER, HIGH, MED Return a structured review report.
- Use severity labels: BLOCKER, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW.
- Only apply fixes after explicit user approval.